WEBVTT

00:18.386 --> 00:21.220
- Hey, it's 5:40
in the morning.

00:21.222 --> 00:24.256
You should go back to bed.

00:24.258 --> 00:27.393
- It's still the end
of the world.

00:27.395 --> 00:30.295
- We'll be safe in Seattle.

00:30.297 --> 00:31.730
- What if Brianna isn't there?

00:31.732 --> 00:33.132
- She will be.

00:33.134 --> 00:34.433
What if she's not?
- She will be.

00:34.435 --> 00:37.603
She will be.
You got to have faith.

00:37.605 --> 00:40.572
- [sighs]
I hate that argument.

00:40.574 --> 00:42.374
- I could hear you snoring
back there.

00:42.376 --> 00:44.676
- You did not.
- Yeah, I did.

00:44.678 --> 00:47.146
Yeah, it was cute.
It sounded like two people.

00:47.148 --> 00:49.281
- Knock it off.
- It did.

00:49.283 --> 00:50.616
It was like a Marine snore.

00:50.618 --> 00:52.785
- [chuckles]

00:52.787 --> 00:55.187
That was somebody else.

00:55.189 --> 00:56.722
- You should go back to bed.

00:56.724 --> 01:00.225
- Don't tell me what to do.

01:00.227 --> 01:03.195
<i> [eerie music]</i>

01:03.197 --> 01:10.169
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:10.171 --> 01:11.503
Josh?

01:11.505 --> 01:16.341
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:16.343 --> 01:19.078
Josh!
- Karen.

01:19.080 --> 01:21.513
It's been like this
for 60 blocks.

01:21.515 --> 01:23.549
There's no blood.
There's no sign of trauma.

01:23.551 --> 01:25.250
Keys left in every car.

01:25.252 --> 01:29.555
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:29.557 --> 01:32.624
Look, it's like--

01:32.626 --> 01:35.461
it's like every single person
in Seattle just suddenly--

01:35.463 --> 01:36.595
- Vanished.

01:42.703 --> 01:45.838
[whispering]
Let's get out of here.

01:45.840 --> 01:48.874
- Hey, Matt, Dana--let's go.

01:50.144 --> 01:51.477
Come on.

01:51.479 --> 01:58.417
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:59.587 --> 02:00.652
[engine turns over]

02:00.654 --> 02:07.593
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:24.678 --> 02:27.646
<i> [ominous music]</i>

02:27.648 --> 02:34.586
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:40.528 --> 02:42.861
- Got some goods here, boys.

02:42.863 --> 02:46.465
- Hey, do you guys think
I could get some food?

02:46.467 --> 02:49.468
- Yeah.
Sure.

02:49.470 --> 02:51.837
We take ass, grass, or cash.

02:51.839 --> 02:54.806
- I call ass.

02:54.808 --> 02:56.708
- Look, dude, I'm starving,
all right?

02:56.710 --> 02:57.876
- And I'm horny.

02:57.878 --> 03:01.213
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:01.215 --> 03:02.548
[gunshot]

03:02.550 --> 03:03.549
- Son of a bitch!

03:03.551 --> 03:04.750
- [panting]

03:04.752 --> 03:06.652
Take it easy.

03:06.654 --> 03:08.320
We're not gonna hurt you.

03:08.322 --> 03:10.789
- Look, dude, take another step,
and I'll blow your nuts off.

03:10.791 --> 03:12.224
Come on, do it.

03:12.226 --> 03:13.692
Do it.

03:13.694 --> 03:15.894
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:15.896 --> 03:17.462
Actually, you know what?

03:17.464 --> 03:18.931
I'll start with you,

03:18.933 --> 03:20.465
since you're so horny.

03:20.467 --> 03:21.800
- Come on, it's okay.
It's okay.

03:21.802 --> 03:25.404
I was just playing.
- Miss?

03:25.406 --> 03:26.405
- What do you want?

03:26.407 --> 03:27.873
- Please don't hurt them.

03:27.875 --> 03:29.241
Come with us.

03:29.243 --> 03:32.644
We have plenty of food.

03:32.646 --> 03:33.845
- Why are you dressed
like that?

03:33.847 --> 03:35.681
- Like what?

03:35.683 --> 03:37.349
- Like Pioneer Village.

03:37.351 --> 03:38.850
- Miss, please.

03:38.852 --> 03:41.820
<i> [tense music]</i>

03:41.822 --> 03:44.656
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:44.658 --> 03:46.225
- Lie face down on the ground.

03:46.227 --> 03:49.528
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:49.530 --> 03:50.963
Do it now!

03:50.965 --> 03:51.997
[gunshot]

03:51.999 --> 03:53.899
<i> [intense music]</i>

03:53.901 --> 03:55.267
- Come on, let's go!

03:55.269 --> 03:57.603
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:57.605 --> 03:58.837
- How fast does this thing go?

03:58.839 --> 03:59.805
- I don't know.

03:59.807 --> 04:02.808
[engine revving]

04:02.810 --> 04:04.343
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:04.345 --> 04:05.611
<i> - Maybe she's here already.</i>

04:05.613 --> 04:06.912
<i> Let's hope to God she is.</i>

04:13.387 --> 04:14.987
Brianna?

04:16.890 --> 04:19.558
- Dad!

04:19.560 --> 04:22.594
- I hope Grandpa's in there.

04:22.596 --> 04:25.030
- Yeah.
Okay.

04:25.032 --> 04:27.899
Stay out here with Sally
and your sister.

04:27.901 --> 04:30.002
- Bri?
- Dad!

04:30.004 --> 04:31.570
- How long could the water
run like that?

04:31.572 --> 04:32.938
- Dad!

04:32.940 --> 04:35.574
- Well, the pumps run
on electricity,

04:35.576 --> 04:36.975
and that's gone.

04:36.977 --> 04:38.877
When the reservoirs run out,
I guess you're done.

04:50.624 --> 04:52.624
- I'll check upstairs.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.026
- All right.
Don't shoot my dad.

05:04.705 --> 05:07.005
- Grandpa's place always
creeps me out.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.774
- Mm-hmm.

05:08.776 --> 05:10.575
He liked the South Pacific.

05:10.577 --> 05:12.511
The Maori, especially.

05:12.513 --> 05:13.712
- They're the ones
that do that--

05:13.714 --> 05:15.314
that war dance with their
tongues out, right?

05:15.316 --> 05:16.782
- The Haka, yeah.
Where'd you see that?

05:16.784 --> 05:18.617
- Rugby teams do it.

05:18.619 --> 05:21.386
- Yeah, that dance is called
the<i> Ak tu et Wanawana.</i>

05:21.388 --> 05:24.022
It means,
"Stand up to the terror."

05:24.024 --> 05:26.391
Here we go.
- Good song for the Apocalypse.

05:28.362 --> 05:29.528
How are the ashes?
- Still warm.

05:29.530 --> 05:31.930
- So he was here, what,
12 hours ago?

05:31.932 --> 05:35.400
- 18, maybe, depending.

05:35.402 --> 05:37.502
Can you go check on
your brother outside?

05:38.906 --> 05:42.341
- Right, check on the football
player with a gun.

05:42.343 --> 05:43.909
But yeah, Dad,
you can be alone.

05:56.523 --> 05:59.558
- All right, old man.

05:59.560 --> 06:00.892
Where the hell did you go?

06:03.097 --> 06:04.663
- They're not inside.

06:04.665 --> 06:06.832
- Well, Briana's still
on the road.

06:06.834 --> 06:09.968
We'll wait here for 'em.

06:09.970 --> 06:12.104
- She's okay, Mom.

06:12.106 --> 06:13.972
If she wasn't, I would know.

06:13.974 --> 06:16.908
[engine rumbling]

06:22.750 --> 06:25.684
- [grunts]
Killed my butt.

06:30.124 --> 06:31.390
What?
What's wrong?

06:31.392 --> 06:34.659
- We don't curse here.

06:34.661 --> 06:36.495
- What do you--
- You said killed,

06:36.497 --> 06:38.130
which breaks the commandment.

06:38.132 --> 06:41.099
And then you said...

06:41.101 --> 06:42.567
well, I can't repeat
what you said,

06:42.569 --> 06:43.869
but it was a vulgar word
for a part of the body

06:43.871 --> 06:45.837
that God made you in.

06:45.839 --> 06:47.906
And then you sinned against
the God that made you.

06:47.908 --> 06:50.675
- Well, I'm not quite
sure that's it, Mary.

06:50.677 --> 06:52.644
- Okay, so what I'm getting
is that you're mad at me

06:52.646 --> 06:53.912
for talking about my butt.

06:53.914 --> 06:55.814
- Stop it!
- Please, Brianna.

06:55.816 --> 06:57.549
Even I think you're
wrong right now.

06:57.551 --> 07:00.552
- Even you?

07:00.554 --> 07:01.853
- Jeez.

07:01.855 --> 07:05.090
- And now you take the Savior's
name in vain.

07:05.092 --> 07:07.526
- What are you--
- You said "jeez."

07:07.528 --> 07:09.161
- I was ready to welcome you,

07:09.163 --> 07:11.596
as we're taught to do.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.499
You're--

07:14.501 --> 07:15.934
I don't know if they'll
even keep you.

07:15.936 --> 07:17.436
I hope they don't.

07:24.778 --> 07:26.745
- Okay, how many people
here are like that?

07:26.747 --> 07:29.748
- All of them.

07:29.750 --> 07:31.183
- Including you?

07:31.185 --> 07:33.452
- Well, I--I guess.

07:33.454 --> 07:34.920
- Okay, look,
I need someone with me

07:34.922 --> 07:36.188
until I get back to my family,

07:36.190 --> 07:37.856
so either it's you, or I
get back on the highway.

07:37.858 --> 07:40.992
Now, are you gonna
be weird with me?

07:40.994 --> 07:42.694
- What's the right answer?

07:42.696 --> 07:43.829
- It's not, Devyn.

07:43.831 --> 07:45.897
You're not gonna
be weird with me.

07:45.899 --> 07:47.165
- Okay.

07:47.167 --> 07:50.068
I'm not gonna be weird with you.

07:50.070 --> 07:53.004
- [whispering] Oh, my God, you
are so gonna be weird with me.

07:53.006 --> 07:54.639
Could you get me some food?

07:54.641 --> 07:56.074
Can you handle that?

07:56.076 --> 07:57.809
- Yeah.

07:57.811 --> 07:59.010
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

08:04.051 --> 08:06.685
- What are you doing?

08:06.687 --> 08:09.721
- [grunts]
We can grow our own food.

08:09.723 --> 08:11.056
- This is my
grandfather's garden.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.090
- Well, he doesn't need these
anymore, sweetie.

08:12.092 --> 08:13.124
We do.

08:13.126 --> 08:14.993
- He's not dead.

08:14.995 --> 08:16.695
You don't know.

08:16.697 --> 08:17.963
- Well, then we'll just borrow
them for a little while

08:17.965 --> 08:19.932
and keep them alive, okay?

08:19.933 --> 08:21.900
Do you want to grab
a bucket over there, please?

08:21.902 --> 08:24.236
[dog barks]

08:24.238 --> 08:25.704
- Did you hear that?

08:25.706 --> 08:27.072
- What?
No.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.510
- It can't be.

08:31.512 --> 08:33.211
Rona?

08:33.213 --> 08:35.547
- Well, Dana, wait!

08:35.549 --> 08:36.615
- Is that you?

08:36.617 --> 08:38.216
[dog snarling]
[screams]

08:38.218 --> 08:40.085
- Dana!

08:40.087 --> 08:41.953
[barking]

08:41.955 --> 08:44.890
<i> [dark music]</i>

08:44.892 --> 08:45.891
Dana!

08:45.893 --> 08:51.563
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:51.565 --> 08:54.232
- [whimpering]

08:54.234 --> 08:55.700
- Dana, are you okay?

08:55.702 --> 08:56.968
Let me see your arm.

08:56.970 --> 08:59.237
- [moaning]

08:59.239 --> 09:01.873
- It's okay.

09:01.875 --> 09:02.941
- What was wrong with her?

09:02.943 --> 09:04.843
- Well, honey,
that dog was rabid.

09:04.845 --> 09:05.844
- What?

09:10.117 --> 09:11.249
All right, all right.

09:11.251 --> 09:12.234
Don't look at that.
Look at me.

09:12.235 --> 09:13.218
Listen to my voice
or something.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.185
La, la, la, la, la.

09:14.187 --> 09:15.253
- Her eyes--

09:15.255 --> 09:16.321
her eyes were all wrong.

09:16.323 --> 09:17.689
They--they were
different colors.

09:17.691 --> 09:19.891
- We need to get
a rabies vaccine ASAP.

09:19.893 --> 09:20.926
- Where, a doctor?

09:20.928 --> 09:22.060
- Does that hurt?
- Yeah.

09:22.062 --> 09:24.829
- Okay, let's make that happen.

09:24.831 --> 09:26.631
- You're--you're sure
she was rabid?

09:26.633 --> 09:28.700
- Oh, honey, she was foaming.
Yeah.

09:28.702 --> 09:31.570
- [panting]
Rabies, that's--that's the--

09:31.572 --> 09:34.039
the one with the needle
in the stomach, right?

09:34.041 --> 09:35.240
The really painful one.

09:35.242 --> 09:36.341
- Yes, it was really painful.

09:36.343 --> 09:38.643
- Okay, well,
let's just, um,

09:38.645 --> 09:40.278
take this one step
at a time, should we?

09:40.280 --> 09:41.313
Let's get you
to the doctor.

09:41.315 --> 09:42.647
- I'm gonna stay here.

09:42.649 --> 09:43.648
Wait for Brianna.

09:43.650 --> 09:44.816
- That's good, Matt.

09:44.818 --> 09:46.751
- [sighs]
- That's good.

09:46.753 --> 09:48.853
Here, here, hold that.
- All right, come on.

09:48.855 --> 09:50.155
- Hold that.
- [groans]

09:50.157 --> 09:51.723
- Come on.

09:51.725 --> 09:53.191
We also need to get
more supplies.

09:53.193 --> 09:54.859
We're running low.

09:54.861 --> 09:58.029
- Righty.
Trade ya.

10:00.033 --> 10:01.967
I want you to scour
this place for everything.

10:01.969 --> 10:04.869
Fuel, ammunition--
everything Grandpa has.

10:04.871 --> 10:06.237
- Got it.

10:06.239 --> 10:08.740
- And don't open that door
unless it's Brianna.

10:08.742 --> 10:10.742
- [scoffs]
Count on it.

10:10.744 --> 10:11.943
- Okay, babe.

10:14.915 --> 10:16.014
<i> - Why do you have a gun?</i>

10:19.720 --> 10:21.620
- I was separated
from my family.

10:21.622 --> 10:23.688
- That was careless.

10:23.690 --> 10:25.724
Did they give you the gun?

10:25.726 --> 10:28.026
- No.

10:28.028 --> 10:30.929
I--I couldn't even
begin to explain it.

10:30.931 --> 10:32.097
Just forget it.

10:32.099 --> 10:33.932
- You've suffered.

10:33.934 --> 10:35.400
- Who hasn't?

10:35.402 --> 10:37.168
I don't know if you've
noticed out here,

10:37.170 --> 10:39.004
but the world's kind
of falling apart.

10:39.006 --> 10:40.271
- That's not a thing
to be feared.

10:40.273 --> 10:42.007
- Mary--
- Well, it isn't.

10:43.310 --> 10:44.943
Trials will lead to mercy.

10:44.945 --> 10:46.778
You'll see.

10:46.780 --> 10:48.413
That's the compact.

10:48.415 --> 10:51.182
All of this proceeds
to order in its time.

10:51.184 --> 10:53.351
- Look, I need to get
to Seattle, all right?

10:53.353 --> 10:54.986
My family's waiting for me
at my grandpa's house.

10:54.988 --> 10:57.055
And...

10:57.057 --> 10:59.658
two weeks ago, I would've gagged
if I had to do that.

10:59.660 --> 11:01.026
All right?

11:01.028 --> 11:02.227
And now I can't wait
to be there.

11:06.700 --> 11:08.967
What?

11:08.969 --> 11:10.935
- The Reverend Brother went
to Seattle two days ago.

11:10.937 --> 11:14.205
- Some of the brethren
had gone to market.

11:14.207 --> 11:15.807
They didn't come back.

11:15.809 --> 11:18.376
- Seattle is not a place
people should go right now.

11:18.378 --> 11:21.946
- It's come to my attention
that you have a weapon.

11:21.948 --> 11:24.249
- Who told you that?

11:24.251 --> 11:25.817
- Give it to me.

11:25.819 --> 11:27.352
- Yeah, I think I'll take
a pass on that one.

11:27.354 --> 11:29.187
- Give it to me
or it will be taken from you,

11:29.189 --> 11:33.024
and you'll be removed
from our community.

11:33.026 --> 11:34.025
- Fine.

11:44.237 --> 11:45.336
- Mary.

11:56.483 --> 11:57.916
You know I'm gonna
need that back.

11:57.918 --> 11:59.784
It could keep me alive.

11:59.786 --> 12:01.720
- All weapons
are forbidden.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.054
- Yeah, well, I'm not kidding.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.190
You're getting it back for me.

12:05.192 --> 12:07.092
Uh, is it okay
if I use this?

12:07.094 --> 12:08.993
- Margaret?

12:08.995 --> 12:11.863
- Maybe go outside
for some privacy.

12:11.865 --> 12:13.431
- Yeah, okay.

12:17.971 --> 12:19.604
- Had enough.

12:19.605 --> 12:21.238
Sally said that if we don't get
the meds by the end of the day,

12:21.241 --> 12:23.441
then Dana's really
gonna be in trouble.

12:23.443 --> 12:25.243
- Well, shouldn't be hard.

12:25.245 --> 12:27.212
The city's empty.

12:27.214 --> 12:30.281
- Yeah, until
the looters get here.

12:30.283 --> 12:32.317
- Hey, right there.

12:32.319 --> 12:33.518
Medical clinic.

12:41.862 --> 12:43.428
- [grunting]

12:52.906 --> 12:53.688
- Come on.

12:53.689 --> 12:54.471
- You know, I don't
have any service,

12:54.474 --> 12:56.274
and I should probably
save my battery anyway,

12:56.276 --> 12:58.376
so forget it.

12:58.378 --> 13:02.080
It's fine.
Don't want to cause any trouble.

13:02.082 --> 13:04.516
- You'll be safe here--

13:04.518 --> 13:05.984
as long as you need.

13:05.986 --> 13:08.953
- This is a time of mercy.

13:08.955 --> 13:10.488
Of course she may stay.

13:16.830 --> 13:18.463
- So you grew up here, huh?

13:18.465 --> 13:21.833
What was that like?
- Uneventful.

13:21.835 --> 13:23.201
- Kind of sounds nice,

13:23.203 --> 13:25.003
considering everything
that's going on.

13:25.005 --> 13:26.838
- Try 15 years of it.

13:26.840 --> 13:27.839
- [chuckles]

13:29.109 --> 13:30.475
- Got it.

13:30.477 --> 13:32.410
- You're kidding.
- Yep.

13:32.412 --> 13:34.245
- Oh, my God, four doses.

13:34.247 --> 13:35.580
Poor Dana.

13:35.582 --> 13:37.982
- We'll break it
to her slowly.

13:37.984 --> 13:39.450
- What's that?

13:39.452 --> 13:41.219
- Uh, it's a 25-year-old Scotch

13:41.221 --> 13:42.821
I found in the back
of the medicine cabinet.

13:42.823 --> 13:45.323
- Really?
- Yeah.

13:45.325 --> 13:47.292
- Cheers.

13:47.294 --> 13:49.894
- Cheers.

13:49.896 --> 13:51.396
Ooh.
I'll get some--

13:51.398 --> 13:52.597
I'm gonna get some needles.

13:52.599 --> 13:53.832
[soft thump]

13:53.834 --> 13:56.568
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

13:56.570 --> 14:03.541
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:07.547 --> 14:09.013
[door creaks]
[footsteps]

14:09.015 --> 14:15.987
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:17.057 --> 14:18.223
[smack]
- [yells]

14:18.225 --> 14:20.024
- Who are you?

14:20.026 --> 14:23.528
- Rawlins.
I'm a doctor.

14:23.530 --> 14:24.863
I know you.

14:24.865 --> 14:25.930
- What do you want?

14:25.932 --> 14:27.298
- Tetracycline.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.200
They're herding all
the Feverheads in one zone.

14:29.202 --> 14:31.402
I need 10,000
doses a week,

14:31.404 --> 14:32.437
never mind new cases.

14:32.439 --> 14:34.038
- Karen, what are you doing?

14:34.040 --> 14:35.373
That's Dr. Rawlins.
Let him up.

14:39.880 --> 14:42.080
- [grunts]

14:42.082 --> 14:44.015
What are you doing here?

14:44.017 --> 14:45.650
- Our daughter was
exposed to rabies.

14:45.652 --> 14:48.019
- Rabies?
That's serious.

14:48.021 --> 14:50.488
- Yeah.
- Want some help?

14:50.490 --> 14:51.956
- I--I can't do this, I--

14:51.958 --> 14:53.191
- Honey, you're gonna be fine.

14:53.193 --> 14:54.626
- No, you can do it.
- Is there any other--

14:54.628 --> 14:56.127
- Just prepare
yourself for pain.

14:56.129 --> 14:57.528
- Is there a pill or something?
- A pill.

14:57.530 --> 14:59.330
- It hurts a little.
It's nothing you can't handle.

14:59.332 --> 15:00.999
- Is this all gonna be--

15:01.001 --> 15:02.233
- Shh, shh.
- I can't do it.

15:02.235 --> 15:04.069
I can't do it.
I can't do it.

15:04.070 --> 15:05.904
- Just about--
- [screaming] Oh, God!

15:05.906 --> 15:07.972
- You're doing great.
- Almost there.

15:07.974 --> 15:09.574
- [crying]
- Almost there.

15:09.576 --> 15:12.076
- You are so close.
- Almost there, almost there.

15:12.078 --> 15:13.578
- So good.
You're such a good girl.

15:13.580 --> 15:14.979
- Almost done, almost done.
- [crying]

15:14.981 --> 15:16.514
- You are unbelievable.

15:16.516 --> 15:17.582
- There you go.
- All done.

15:17.584 --> 15:18.783
- Baby, you're all done.
- All done.

15:18.784 --> 15:19.983
- You did it.
- Keep pressure on that.

15:19.986 --> 15:21.686
- Thank you, doctor.
- You're welcome.

15:21.687 --> 15:23.387
- All right, sweetie,
put this right here.

15:23.390 --> 15:25.390
- She'll be fine.
- You were amazing.

15:25.392 --> 15:27.025
Doc, we've got to get you
to your car.

15:27.027 --> 15:27.992
There're gonna be looters.

15:27.994 --> 15:28.993
- No one's gonna shoot me

15:28.995 --> 15:29.994
between here and there.

15:29.996 --> 15:31.129
- You don't know that.

15:31.131 --> 15:32.096
- I got you.
- I'll be right back.

15:32.098 --> 15:34.332
- Oh.
- You were so brave.

15:34.334 --> 15:36.301
- Take care.
- Bye. Thanks, doc.

15:36.303 --> 15:37.502
- Well done.
Well done, honey.

15:37.504 --> 15:40.004
Only three left.

15:40.006 --> 15:42.340
- That's good.
- You did so well.

15:42.342 --> 15:43.975
- [exhales]

16:22.015 --> 16:24.248
[creaking]

16:30.290 --> 16:31.522
[heavy thump]

16:34.294 --> 16:35.259
[cocks rifle]

16:39.499 --> 16:42.467
<i> [tense music]</i>

16:42.469 --> 16:49.440
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:59.152 --> 17:00.618
[door creaks]

17:00.620 --> 17:07.592
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:27.547 --> 17:29.347
- [gasps]

17:29.349 --> 17:31.315
[panting]

17:33.119 --> 17:34.719
- What the hell are you
doing down here?

17:34.721 --> 17:37.355
- I'm in terrible trouble.

17:37.357 --> 17:39.290
I hope you won't
make me leave.

17:41.327 --> 17:43.494
- Um...

17:43.496 --> 17:45.396
I'm not gonna make you leave.

17:58.678 --> 18:01.245
- Why are we stopping?

18:01.247 --> 18:02.547
- News van.

18:02.549 --> 18:04.282
[gunshots]
- Oh, my God.

18:04.284 --> 18:06.084
Gunshots?
Is this really the time?

18:06.086 --> 18:07.718
- Three million people are gone,
including my father, Karen.

18:07.720 --> 18:08.853
I need to know what happened.

18:08.855 --> 18:10.221
[gunshots]

18:10.223 --> 18:15.259
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:15.261 --> 18:17.195
Here.
Here.

18:17.197 --> 18:19.664
Here, look.

18:19.666 --> 18:21.399
- What is it?

18:21.401 --> 18:23.668
<i> - We don't know what's</i>
<i> happening yet, Christine,</i>

18:23.670 --> 18:26.671
<i> but panic has swept the city</i>
<i> for ten minutes now, and--</i>

18:26.673 --> 18:28.139
<i> [gunshot]</i>

18:28.141 --> 18:29.707
<i> Oh, my God.</i>

18:29.709 --> 18:33.144
<i> And rumors say that--</i>

18:33.146 --> 18:34.312
<i> oh, my God.</i>

18:34.314 --> 18:36.481
<i> Are those people?</i>

18:36.483 --> 18:38.449
<i> No, no, don't tell me</i>
<i> those are people!</i>

18:38.451 --> 18:40.518
<i> Oh, my God, it's here!</i>

18:40.520 --> 18:42.253
<i> Oh, Jesus, it's here!</i>

18:42.255 --> 18:43.454
<i> [screams]</i>

18:43.456 --> 18:44.789
<i> Tell everyone it's here!</i>

18:44.791 --> 18:45.723
<i> [static crackles]</i>

18:47.861 --> 18:50.595
- What?
What is it?

18:50.597 --> 18:51.696
- I don't know.

19:00.406 --> 19:01.906
- Matt. Matt?
<i> [p</i> h<i> - Yeah, Mom?ling]</i>

19:01.908 --> 19:04.509
- Honey, honey, honey,
have you--

19:04.511 --> 19:05.810
<i>have you heard from Brianna?</i>

19:05.812 --> 19:07.411
- Not yet.
I'm watching for her.

19:07.413 --> 19:08.446
Everything's fine.

19:08.448 --> 19:09.714
<i> - That does not sound fine.</i>

19:09.716 --> 19:10.882
<i> What's going on?</i>
- It's fine.

19:10.884 --> 19:12.583
Everything's fine.
It's all fine.

19:12.585 --> 19:14.519
- Matt.

19:14.521 --> 19:15.853
- How are you?
[clears throat]

19:15.855 --> 19:16.921
- What's g--Matt?

19:16.923 --> 19:18.723
<i> [line beeping]</i>

19:31.938 --> 19:34.805
- Are you still cold, miss...

19:34.807 --> 19:37.241
- I'm Ala.

19:37.243 --> 19:39.911
- Matt.

19:39.913 --> 19:43.648
Are you still cold, Ala?

19:43.650 --> 19:46.884
- No, much better.
Thank you...

19:46.886 --> 19:50.421
Matt.

19:50.423 --> 19:51.622
- Well, I don't want
to be rude, but, uh--

19:51.624 --> 19:54.659
- What was I doing
in your basement?

19:54.661 --> 19:56.961
- Sure.
Let's start with that.

19:58.798 --> 20:00.965
- I'm running away

20:00.967 --> 20:02.200
from my husband.

20:02.202 --> 20:04.468
- Naked?

20:04.470 --> 20:06.671
- He went...

20:06.673 --> 20:08.272
crazy.

20:08.274 --> 20:09.974
It was bad.
I ran and hid.

20:09.976 --> 20:13.811
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

20:13.813 --> 20:16.547
- You know where...

20:16.549 --> 20:18.382
anyone else is?

20:18.384 --> 20:19.817
Where they went?

20:19.819 --> 20:21.986
- No.

20:21.988 --> 20:25.556
I'm not from here.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.425
I'm worried he'll find me.

20:27.427 --> 20:28.926
He can't find me.
He can't.

20:28.928 --> 20:30.728
- Shh, shh, it's okay.

20:30.730 --> 20:32.396
I can protect you.
- You don't know--

20:32.398 --> 20:33.864
- I promise.
- You don't know what he's like.

20:33.866 --> 20:35.766
So angry.

20:38.538 --> 20:41.706
- I think...

20:41.708 --> 20:43.241
we can calm him down.

20:47.614 --> 20:49.614
- You can tell me, you know.

20:49.616 --> 20:51.882
- What?
Tell you what?

20:51.884 --> 20:53.684
- What it is you don't
want to tell me.

20:53.686 --> 20:55.886
- It's nothing.
I...

20:55.888 --> 20:57.288
- Come on.

20:59.626 --> 21:01.492
- All right.
[clears throat]

21:01.494 --> 21:04.328
When I powered up the--
the news trucks,

21:04.330 --> 21:05.863
they were, uh,
recording live.

21:05.865 --> 21:08.799
They all these feeds from all
these different cable nets.

21:08.801 --> 21:10.901
All the feeds went dead
at the same time.

21:12.505 --> 21:13.804
- Meaning...

21:13.806 --> 21:15.973
- Well, everything
that's happening here

21:15.975 --> 21:17.308
is happening everywhere.

21:19.846 --> 21:22.713
- Everywhere?
- New York, Chicago, L.A., D.C.

21:22.715 --> 21:24.015
Those are the ones
I know about.

21:28.655 --> 21:32.323
- Okay, I'm gonna absorb that
when I have more time.

21:32.325 --> 21:34.358
Let's, uh--

21:34.360 --> 21:35.860
let's pull in here
and get some supplies.

21:42.335 --> 21:44.769
Come on, guys.
Let's go.

21:47.807 --> 21:49.607
- In and out,
fast as we can.

21:55.782 --> 21:57.381
- I should probably
get back on the road.

21:57.383 --> 21:59.917
- No.
It's not safe.

21:59.919 --> 22:01.886
- It doesn't matter, Devyn.
They're waiting for me.

22:01.888 --> 22:04.689
Does your, um...

22:04.691 --> 22:07.958
group have a car?

22:07.960 --> 22:09.093
- Two of 'em.

22:09.095 --> 22:10.461
- Do you think you
could drive me?

22:10.463 --> 22:12.496
- I would.

22:12.498 --> 22:14.432
[sighs]

22:14.434 --> 22:15.633
The group that went to Seattle

22:15.635 --> 22:16.934
disappeared with one of them.

22:16.936 --> 22:18.936
And the Reverend Brother
has the other.

22:18.938 --> 22:21.405
But he's generous.
When he returns--

22:21.407 --> 22:23.874
[rushing sound]

22:23.876 --> 22:25.576
[cows mooing]

22:25.578 --> 22:27.111
What was that?

22:27.113 --> 22:28.813
- I've heard that sound before.

22:28.815 --> 22:31.749
[rushing sound]

22:32.919 --> 22:34.085
- What is that?

22:34.087 --> 22:35.786
- I know what that is.

22:35.788 --> 22:37.955
Get in the barn, now!

22:37.957 --> 22:40.024
Everyone get in the barn!

22:40.026 --> 22:41.859
- Run!
Hurry!

22:41.861 --> 22:44.128
[shrieking]

22:47.700 --> 22:49.567
- Two full boxes
of tetracycline.

22:49.569 --> 22:52.002
- Oh, God.
Thank God.

22:52.004 --> 22:53.137
Oh, here.

22:53.139 --> 22:54.772
Already loaded.

22:54.774 --> 22:56.774
- Well, that's why
I married you.

22:56.776 --> 22:57.975
Body armor?
Really?

22:57.977 --> 23:00.678
- Yeah, it's a his and hers.

23:00.680 --> 23:02.380
- Oh, hey.
- Hey, that's cyanide.

23:02.382 --> 23:03.781
What are you doing,
fumigating things?

23:03.783 --> 23:05.649
- Yeah, well, they say there's

23:05.651 --> 23:07.151
gonna be a plague
of locusts, right?

23:07.153 --> 23:08.586
- It's weird how you
think that's funny.

23:08.588 --> 23:10.054
- Dana, get another cart.

23:10.056 --> 23:12.056
- Great.
We'll concentrate on junk food.

23:12.058 --> 23:15.159
[rattling]
- Shh.

23:15.161 --> 23:17.061
- [whispering]
We're not alone.

23:17.063 --> 23:20.030
<i> [tense music]</i>

23:20.032 --> 23:23.501
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:23.503 --> 23:26.737
- Don't move.
Put your weapons on the floor.

23:26.739 --> 23:28.172
- We're--we're leaving
the store.

23:28.174 --> 23:29.740
You can have the whole
thing to yourself.

23:29.742 --> 23:31.575
- We only want
the tetracycline.

23:31.577 --> 23:34.412
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:34.414 --> 23:35.446
- We'll split it with you.

23:35.448 --> 23:37.448
- We're taking all of it, bitch.

23:37.450 --> 23:39.717
[gunshots]

23:43.423 --> 23:44.655
- [whispering]
What do you think?

23:44.657 --> 23:45.623
I think this

23:45.625 --> 23:48.659
[gunfire]

23:48.661 --> 23:52.029
<i> [tense music]</i>

23:52.031 --> 23:53.164
Take the cart out back.

23:53.166 --> 23:54.698
You guys stay here.
- Okay.

23:54.700 --> 23:57.968
- On three, two, one.

23:57.970 --> 24:00.905
[gunfire]

24:04.844 --> 24:06.143
[both whimpering]

24:06.145 --> 24:09.947
[gunshots]

24:09.949 --> 24:12.917
- Hey.
Hey.

24:12.919 --> 24:15.586
Take Dana.
Stay low.

24:15.588 --> 24:17.822
Wait till I fire.

24:17.824 --> 24:19.590
Okay.

24:19.592 --> 24:22.226
[gunfire]

24:22.228 --> 24:23.227
- Go.

24:23.229 --> 24:25.830
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:25.832 --> 24:29.733
[gunfire]

24:29.735 --> 24:31.635
[bullets whizzing]

24:31.637 --> 24:34.638
- [screaming]

24:34.640 --> 24:41.612
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:51.791 --> 24:52.857
[can clattering]

24:52.859 --> 24:53.858
[gunshots]

24:53.860 --> 24:54.859
- [yells]

24:54.861 --> 24:57.795
[moaning]

24:59.198 --> 25:04.068
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:04.070 --> 25:05.202
- Dana, what are you doing?

25:05.204 --> 25:07.204
You can't!
[screams]

25:07.206 --> 25:14.144
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:26.792 --> 25:27.892
[smack]
- [grunts]

25:27.894 --> 25:30.895
[panting]

25:30.897 --> 25:37.635
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:37.637 --> 25:40.070
- Where are Sally and Dana?

25:40.072 --> 25:41.705
- In the trailer.

25:41.707 --> 25:44.542
- [panting]

25:44.544 --> 25:45.676
Where's Dana?

25:45.678 --> 25:46.977
- Isn't she with you?

25:46.979 --> 25:48.646
- No, she's supposed
to be with you.

25:48.648 --> 25:50.781
- No, she grabbed a gun
and went to find you!

25:50.783 --> 25:52.082
- What, you didn't stop her?

25:52.084 --> 25:54.852
- I couldn't stop her!
She wanted to help you!

25:54.854 --> 25:56.887
- Who cares what she wants?
She's 16!

25:56.889 --> 25:58.622
- This is not my fault.

25:58.624 --> 26:00.991
This is what happens when
we embrace a gun culture!

26:00.993 --> 26:03.227
<i> [intercom feedback]</i>
<i> - Attention, big box shoppers.</i>

26:03.229 --> 26:05.829
<i> We have your little girl.</i>

26:05.831 --> 26:09.300
<i> So you give us all</i>
<i> the tetracycline,</i>

26:09.302 --> 26:11.735
<i> or we hang up</i>
<i> your little girl</i>

26:11.737 --> 26:13.771
<i> and cut her throat.</i>

26:13.773 --> 26:15.706
Tell them how big
the knife is, sweetie.

26:18.744 --> 26:20.311
- No.

26:20.313 --> 26:22.846
<i> - Tell them</i>
<i> or I'll cut you now.</i>

26:23.916 --> 26:26.584
- Mom, Dad, I'm sorry.

26:26.586 --> 26:28.886
- It's okay, baby!
We're coming in after you!

26:28.888 --> 26:31.221
- That's a bad idea,
and you know it.

26:31.223 --> 26:33.891
You got five minutes
to figure this out.

26:35.127 --> 26:42.132
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:42.134 --> 26:44.902
[growling]

26:44.904 --> 26:46.270
- Oh, no.

26:46.272 --> 26:48.639
- Shh, shh, shh.

26:48.641 --> 26:50.307
[growling]

26:50.309 --> 26:52.309
- I see it.
I see the demon!

26:52.311 --> 26:53.744
- What have you brought upon us?

26:53.746 --> 26:54.812
- I didn't do anything!

26:57.383 --> 27:00.751
[growling]

27:00.753 --> 27:01.752
- What was that?

27:01.754 --> 27:03.854
A flying demon?

27:03.856 --> 27:05.789
Oh, my God!

27:05.791 --> 27:07.625
[smash]

27:07.627 --> 27:10.227
- Dear Lord, please let
this evil pass from us.

27:10.229 --> 27:11.362
[guttural noises]

27:11.364 --> 27:13.063
[screams]

27:14.634 --> 27:15.866
- We're gonna go in shooting.

27:15.868 --> 27:16.934
- What?
They'll kill us all.

27:16.936 --> 27:17.935
I don't want your gun.

27:17.937 --> 27:19.170
- You don't have a vote.

27:19.171 --> 27:20.404
- Listen, let it go,
Karen, okay? Move on.

27:20.406 --> 27:21.772
- You want to be
my human shield?

27:21.774 --> 27:23.040
- Sally's right.
That's a bad idea.

27:23.042 --> 27:24.274
- So what do you want to do?

27:24.276 --> 27:26.143
- To actually give them
what they want.

27:26.145 --> 27:27.878
- That's a terrible idea.
- Listen.

27:27.880 --> 27:30.147
You're a warrior.
They're warriors too.

27:30.149 --> 27:31.315
They're gonna read you
as a threat,

27:31.317 --> 27:32.650
and they know how
to respond to threats.

27:32.652 --> 27:33.784
Maybe you can kill
one or two of them,

27:33.786 --> 27:35.252
but they're gonna
hit Dana first.

27:35.253 --> 27:36.719
Me, on the other hand--
I'm non-threatening.

27:36.722 --> 27:38.956
I'm more like a--
like a priest,

27:38.958 --> 27:40.324
I guess,
without the celibacy part.

27:40.326 --> 27:41.992
- They're gonna kill the weak.

27:41.994 --> 27:43.193
- I'm not weak.

27:43.195 --> 27:44.361
I'm just non-threatening.

27:46.699 --> 27:48.766
I'm gonna go get
our baby back.

27:48.768 --> 27:50.100
You got to trust me, Karen.

27:54.306 --> 27:55.239
If I'm not out
in five minutes,

27:55.241 --> 27:56.240
come get me.

27:57.743 --> 27:59.443
Oh, do you have a lighter?

28:01.447 --> 28:03.714
[crashing]

28:03.716 --> 28:05.282
<i> [dark music]</i>

28:05.284 --> 28:06.750
- He's here.
He found me.

28:06.752 --> 28:08.719
- Stay here.
- Okay.

28:08.721 --> 28:11.121
- [indistinct muttering]

28:11.123 --> 28:14.124
[growling]

28:14.126 --> 28:18.729
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:18.731 --> 28:19.897
- [screams]

28:19.899 --> 28:22.399
- [yelling gibberish]

28:22.401 --> 28:27.938
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:27.940 --> 28:29.106
- [growling]
- [screams]

28:29.108 --> 28:30.908
- [yells]

28:30.910 --> 28:32.776
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:32.778 --> 28:36.046
- [screams]
Stop!

28:36.048 --> 28:37.981
No, no!

28:37.983 --> 28:39.283
[gunshot]

28:39.285 --> 28:40.951
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:40.953 --> 28:44.755
[gunshots]

28:44.757 --> 28:46.890
- [growling]

28:48.027 --> 28:49.026
- [gasps]

28:49.028 --> 28:51.929
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:51.931 --> 28:53.163
What the hell was that?

28:55.267 --> 28:57.167
Oh.

28:57.169 --> 28:59.203
Oh, that smell.

28:59.205 --> 29:01.772
What the hell was that?

29:01.774 --> 29:04.408
You said you were trying to
get away from your husband.

29:04.410 --> 29:06.343
- That was my husband.

29:06.345 --> 29:09.046
<i> [intense music]</i>

29:25.131 --> 29:27.998
Tetracycline.
- Dana,Unopened. scared.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.200
- What's in the other bag?

29:30.202 --> 29:32.069
- The other bag.
Uh, well...

29:36.942 --> 29:38.475
- It's a Molotov!
Shoot him!

29:38.477 --> 29:40.144
- Whoa, whoa, guys, it's already
too late to shoot me.

29:40.146 --> 29:41.812
- Why?

29:41.814 --> 29:43.981
- 'Cause if I drop the Molotov
into the ammo box,

29:43.983 --> 29:45.949
it's filled with
ammonium nitrate

29:45.951 --> 29:47.117
and lamp oil.

29:47.119 --> 29:48.852
- It's a fertilizer bomb.

29:48.854 --> 29:50.921
- [chuckles]
Kind of incredible.

29:50.923 --> 29:53.824
I find it all in the store.

29:53.826 --> 29:55.425
So if I drop the bottle,

29:55.427 --> 29:57.094
we all go boom!

29:57.096 --> 29:59.363
<i> [tense music]</i>

29:59.365 --> 30:01.465
Be a big mist
of blood and brains.

30:01.467 --> 30:03.333
Now, you can have
the tetracycline.

30:03.335 --> 30:04.835
That's good.

30:04.837 --> 30:06.503
I just want my daughter first.

30:06.505 --> 30:08.539
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:08.541 --> 30:09.873
Otherwise, you know,

30:09.875 --> 30:11.809
we all paint the walls.

30:11.811 --> 30:13.510
- If we die, you die.

30:13.512 --> 30:15.412
- Yeah, but you want
to live more than I do,

30:15.414 --> 30:17.447
'cause I really don't want to
live without my little girl.

30:17.449 --> 30:22.486
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:22.488 --> 30:24.955
Tick-tock!
What do you say?

30:24.957 --> 30:26.089
Ooh!

30:26.091 --> 30:28.826
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:28.828 --> 30:30.994
- Okay, smart guy,
here she comes.

30:30.996 --> 30:31.995
- Uh-huh.

30:31.997 --> 30:33.931
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:33.933 --> 30:34.932
Hey.

30:34.934 --> 30:36.266
- Stop!

30:36.268 --> 30:38.836
The meds!
Now!

30:38.838 --> 30:40.337
- The meds now.

30:40.339 --> 30:43.073
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:43.075 --> 30:44.608
Okay.

30:44.610 --> 30:47.344
Here we go.
Here we go.

30:47.346 --> 30:48.345
Dana, when I throw the bag,

30:48.347 --> 30:49.346
you come to me, all right?

30:49.348 --> 30:52.115
One, two...

30:52.117 --> 30:54.518
three.

30:54.520 --> 30:55.986
Come here.

30:55.988 --> 30:58.121
- Dad, I'm so sorry!
- It's okay.

30:58.123 --> 30:59.122
It'll be over in a minute,
I promise.

30:59.124 --> 31:00.257
- Okay.

31:00.259 --> 31:01.158
- I want you to get out
of the store.

31:01.160 --> 31:02.226
Get out.

31:02.228 --> 31:04.862
- Yeah?
- Yeah, yeah.

31:04.864 --> 31:05.996
- Okay, okay, guys.

31:05.998 --> 31:07.564
It's there, right?

31:07.566 --> 31:10.934
We don't have to be
uncivilized about this.

31:10.936 --> 31:14.004
I could just wait here,
and you could take off, and--

31:14.006 --> 31:15.505
or I could just carry
this bomb out of here,

31:15.507 --> 31:19.009
but you know what
I'd like to do?

31:19.011 --> 31:20.444
Look at this.

31:20.446 --> 31:21.879
[cork pops]
Look at that.

31:21.881 --> 31:24.514
That's a 25-year-old
single malt Scotch.

31:24.516 --> 31:25.549
You ever had that?
That's one of the finest

31:25.551 --> 31:26.917
things in the world.

31:26.919 --> 31:28.385
Lochbrae.

31:28.387 --> 31:29.920
One of the rarest, and they
ain't making it anymore.

31:29.922 --> 31:30.921
[chuckles]

31:30.923 --> 31:32.155
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:32.157 --> 31:35.092
What do you say?

31:35.094 --> 31:36.293
Let's have a toast.

31:36.295 --> 31:38.595
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:38.597 --> 31:40.564
To all that was.

31:40.566 --> 31:42.933
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:42.935 --> 31:44.902
- Go.
Go.

31:44.904 --> 31:48.171
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:48.173 --> 31:50.974
- Easy.
Easy, Tiger.

31:50.976 --> 31:54.478
Come on.
Come here.

31:54.480 --> 31:56.446
Come on.

31:56.448 --> 31:58.081
Let's have a toast.

32:00.619 --> 32:02.386
- Here.

32:08.527 --> 32:11.028
- To...

32:11.030 --> 32:13.630
to everything that once was

32:13.632 --> 32:15.332
'cause it ain't coming back.

32:15.334 --> 32:17.100
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:17.102 --> 32:18.568
- All right.

32:18.570 --> 32:23.974
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:23.976 --> 32:26.310
- Mmm.
- Ahh.

32:26.312 --> 32:27.444
- Oh.
- [sighs]

32:27.446 --> 32:29.646
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:29.648 --> 32:30.614
- That's sweet.

32:33.118 --> 32:35.519
- Everything I told you is true.

32:35.521 --> 32:36.987
That was my husband.

32:36.989 --> 32:38.255
I was running from him.

32:38.257 --> 32:40.390
You saved me.

32:40.392 --> 32:43.360
<i> [ominous music]</i>

32:43.362 --> 32:44.428
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:44.430 --> 32:46.496
- Where do you come from?

32:46.498 --> 32:49.099
- New Zealand, off the coast.

32:49.101 --> 32:50.133
- That's far from here.

32:50.135 --> 32:52.002
- Not if you're me

32:52.004 --> 32:53.704
or my husband.

32:53.706 --> 32:55.205
- How did he get in here?

32:55.207 --> 32:57.474
- You wouldn't
understand it, Matt.

32:57.476 --> 32:58.642
You're very brave,

32:58.644 --> 33:00.143
and I'm in your debt.

33:00.145 --> 33:03.380
- I think you should just stay
right over there.

33:03.382 --> 33:06.149
- Are you sure?

33:06.151 --> 33:09.219
I have to thank you, Matt.

33:09.221 --> 33:11.088
No one's ever been
that nice to me.

33:11.090 --> 33:12.689
- Your husband turned
into a--

33:12.691 --> 33:15.158
then just...

33:15.160 --> 33:16.426
disintegrated.

33:20.099 --> 33:23.033
- As he deserved.

33:23.035 --> 33:24.301
Thank you, Matt.

33:24.303 --> 33:27.270
<i> [eerie music]</i>

33:27.272 --> 33:30.674
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:30.676 --> 33:31.675
- This is too much.

33:31.677 --> 33:33.410
[clears throat]

33:33.412 --> 33:36.313
Uh...

33:36.315 --> 33:38.582
- You're kind.

33:38.584 --> 33:40.150
I'm surprised.

33:40.152 --> 33:41.585
Not like him at all.

33:41.587 --> 33:48.558
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:49.561 --> 33:50.794
Here it is.

33:50.796 --> 33:57.734
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:59.338 --> 34:00.604
- That's my grandpa's.

34:00.606 --> 34:02.639
- No, it's not.

34:02.641 --> 34:05.075
It was never his to take.

34:05.077 --> 34:07.577
I came here to get it back.

34:07.579 --> 34:08.545
- Did you know him?

34:08.547 --> 34:10.380
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:10.382 --> 34:11.715
- Yes.

34:11.717 --> 34:12.682
- How well?

34:12.684 --> 34:16.053
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:16.055 --> 34:19.556
- Enough to know his
smell on this shirt.

34:19.558 --> 34:22.559
He wanted to possess things.

34:22.561 --> 34:24.661
He thought everything was his.

34:24.663 --> 34:27.764
- What happened to him?

34:27.766 --> 34:31.568
Do you know?

34:31.570 --> 34:33.470
- Close your eyes
and turn around.

34:33.472 --> 34:35.806
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:35.808 --> 34:38.375
You really should.

34:38.377 --> 34:39.476
Trust me.

34:39.478 --> 34:46.416
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:49.254 --> 34:52.322
I'm giving you whatever you
want most in the world, Matt.

34:52.324 --> 34:53.457
You decide.

34:53.459 --> 34:54.758
[slithering sound]

34:54.760 --> 34:56.593
[loud hiss]

35:12.211 --> 35:14.111
- Be honest with me.
- Ahh.

35:14.113 --> 35:15.612
- You ever tasted
anything like that?

35:15.614 --> 35:17.314
- [laughs]
No, I haven't.

35:17.316 --> 35:20.617
- Yeah.
[all laughing]

35:20.619 --> 35:21.785
That mean you're
not gonna kill me?

35:21.787 --> 35:24.788
[all laughing]

35:24.790 --> 35:27.757
<i> [dark music]</i>

35:27.759 --> 35:30.127
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:30.129 --> 35:32.462
[both coughing]

35:32.464 --> 35:34.764
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:34.766 --> 35:36.766
- What the hell?

35:36.768 --> 35:38.201
[glass shatters]

35:38.203 --> 35:39.803
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:39.805 --> 35:40.804
- [exclaims]

35:40.806 --> 35:42.139
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:42.141 --> 35:43.373
- [gagging]

35:43.375 --> 35:50.313
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:56.188 --> 35:59.322
- [groaning]

35:59.324 --> 36:06.296
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:08.333 --> 36:11.334
[rasping]

36:11.336 --> 36:12.335
[grunts]

36:12.337 --> 36:15.772
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:15.774 --> 36:17.240
<i> - I'm not weak.</i>

36:17.242 --> 36:19.309
<i> Just non-threatening.</i>

36:19.311 --> 36:25.315
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:25.317 --> 36:27.517
[all groaning]

36:27.519 --> 36:29.886
- [whispering]
Dad...

36:29.888 --> 36:31.454
Dad, what did you do?

36:31.456 --> 36:33.723
- Just, uh, you know--

36:33.725 --> 36:36.259
I told you, you had
to be ready for locusts.

36:36.261 --> 36:37.627
- What does that mean?

36:37.629 --> 36:41.264
- I put cyanide from
the bug spray into their drinks.

36:41.266 --> 36:43.867
- And now they're dying?

36:43.869 --> 36:45.702
My God, Dad,
they were letting us go.

36:45.704 --> 36:48.205
- No, they weren't.
They were gonna kill me.

36:48.207 --> 36:49.606
Then they were gonna kill you.

36:49.608 --> 36:53.510
[muffled groans]

36:53.512 --> 36:55.245
And then they were gonna
kill Mom and Aunt Sally.

37:03.388 --> 37:05.555
Could you, uh, please not
tell your mother about this?

37:08.627 --> 37:10.660
[indistinct chatter]

37:17.236 --> 37:18.468
- I think it's gone.

37:18.470 --> 37:19.803
- Dev, we don't know that.

37:19.805 --> 37:21.671
- We need to find the others,

37:21.673 --> 37:24.374
make sure they're okay.

37:24.376 --> 37:25.675
- No, you cannot go outside.

37:25.677 --> 37:26.710
It could still be there.

37:26.712 --> 37:28.345
- We haven't heard it
in a while.

37:28.347 --> 37:30.914
- I need to know
everyone else is safe.

37:30.916 --> 37:33.483
- Devyn.
Damn it!

37:33.485 --> 37:34.985
- Would you stop your profanity?

37:34.987 --> 37:36.486
- Rachel!
Sarah!

37:36.488 --> 37:37.721
- You're not listening to me!

37:37.723 --> 37:38.755
- It's gone, all right?

37:38.757 --> 37:40.390
It passed over us;
we're delivered.

37:40.392 --> 37:42.592
[shrieking]

37:42.594 --> 37:43.727
- Shit, I told you.

37:43.729 --> 37:45.562
- This is what comes
of your blasphemy!

37:45.564 --> 37:46.730
- Get down!

37:46.732 --> 37:47.931
Get down, lie still!

37:47.933 --> 37:49.966
[shrieking]

37:49.968 --> 37:52.936
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

37:52.938 --> 37:55.772
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:55.774 --> 37:59.342
[bellowing]

37:59.344 --> 38:00.844
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:00.846 --> 38:03.780
[shrieking]

38:09.821 --> 38:11.988
- It was coming to take her.

38:11.990 --> 38:14.724
But it recognized her.

38:14.726 --> 38:15.792
- That's just crazy.

38:24.336 --> 38:27.304
<i> -</i> S<i> Just pop the clutchret,</i>
<i> and lay a patch,</i>

38:27.306 --> 38:30.073
<i> and let it all</i>
<i> slide down the hatch.</i>

38:30.075 --> 38:33.510
<i> We got more days</i>
<i> in the rearview than ahead.</i>

38:33.512 --> 38:36.079
<i> So how 'bout we tromp it</i>
<i> right now</i>

38:36.081 --> 38:38.381
<i> with some Ben and Sweets--</i>

38:38.383 --> 38:41.084
<i> [static crackling]</i>

38:55.767 --> 38:58.668
[cell phone ringing]

39:02.874 --> 39:04.541
- Brianna.
<i> - Matt!</i>

39:04.543 --> 39:05.608
- [whispering]
Oh, my God.

39:05.610 --> 39:07.077
Where are you?

39:07.079 --> 39:08.912
- Uh, I'm in this
weird commune.

39:08.914 --> 39:11.448
Northeast, 40 miles off Road 18,

39:11.450 --> 39:14.718
<i> on the--on the farm road.</i>

39:14.720 --> 39:15.919
<i> Matt, my battery's dying.</i>

39:15.921 --> 39:17.987
- Okay, speak faster.
Where?

39:17.989 --> 39:20.123
<i> - The site is near Redmond,</i>
<i> and Road 18</i>

39:20.125 --> 39:21.658
<i> connects there with 204 East.</i>

39:21.660 --> 39:23.059
- 204 East.

39:23.061 --> 39:24.427
<i> - Turn north there,</i>
<i> and head towards Sultan.</i>

39:24.429 --> 39:25.695
- To Sultan.
<i> - Yes.</i>

39:25.697 --> 39:26.930
- Okay, got it.
<i> - Matt?</i>

39:26.932 --> 39:28.098
- And Bri--
<i> - Matt, Matt,</i>

39:28.100 --> 39:29.566
<i> you're breaking up.</i>
- Bri!

39:29.568 --> 39:30.900
Bri!
<i> [line beeping]</i>

39:36.875 --> 39:38.908
"I'm giving you whatever
you want most in the world."

39:41.480 --> 39:45.415
- Matt?
- Did you get through?

39:45.417 --> 39:46.549
- Yeah, I did for a second.

39:48.720 --> 39:49.919
They know where I am now, Devyn.

39:49.921 --> 39:50.954
They're coming for me.

39:50.956 --> 39:52.122
- Good.

39:57.929 --> 39:59.529
[RV horn honks]

40:11.510 --> 40:13.410
- Okay, let's go.

40:13.412 --> 40:14.511
- Where is she?

40:14.513 --> 40:15.879
- She's at a commune
off Road 18.

40:15.881 --> 40:17.714
Okay, um, head to Redmond;

40:17.716 --> 40:19.916
cut east for about ten miles.

40:19.918 --> 40:20.884
- That's great.

40:22.654 --> 40:24.053
So, I mean, how did she sound?

40:24.055 --> 40:25.722
- Great.
- Good.

40:25.724 --> 40:26.790
- She was bossy.

40:26.792 --> 40:28.425
- She was bossy.
- Old Brianna.

40:28.427 --> 40:30.827
- That's a good sign.

40:30.829 --> 40:31.895
- Where's Mom?

40:31.897 --> 40:32.896
- She's asleep in the back.

40:32.898 --> 40:34.898
She's had a big night.

40:34.900 --> 40:36.132
- I bet.

40:36.134 --> 40:38.535
- How are you?

40:38.537 --> 40:40.603
- Pretty quiet until she called.

40:40.605 --> 40:42.439
- Thank God.
Thank God she called.

40:45.043 --> 40:46.776
- You ever heard of a Ponaturi?

40:46.778 --> 40:49.979
- Yeah.
Where'd you pick that up?

40:49.981 --> 40:52.215
- Just one of Grandpa's books,
you know.

40:52.217 --> 40:54.784
What else was I gonna do?
It was--

40:54.786 --> 40:58.888
- Like a South Sea, uh,
kind of a sea goblin creature.

40:58.890 --> 41:00.857
It's a Maori legend.

41:00.859 --> 41:03.193
- Oh.

41:03.195 --> 41:05.061
- It's amphibious.
It lives under the water,

41:05.063 --> 41:08.565
and at night it comes
to the land to sleep.

41:09.835 --> 41:12.168
And it'll suck your bones out--

41:12.170 --> 41:14.537
take them back to the ocean.

41:14.539 --> 41:16.706
- Holy shit.
- Yeah.

41:16.708 --> 41:18.708
It was one of your
grandpa's favorites.

41:18.710 --> 41:19.943
Whenever I did anything
he didn't like,

41:19.945 --> 41:21.110
he'd always tell me that,

41:21.112 --> 41:22.078
"The Ponaturi's gonna
come get you,

41:22.080 --> 41:24.080
suck your bones out tonight."

41:24.082 --> 41:27.684
Used to frighten the hell out
of me when I was a little kid.

41:27.686 --> 41:29.986
Your grandpa always had a way
of taking it too far.

41:32.224 --> 41:33.957
Next you're gonna tell me
you saw one.

41:33.959 --> 41:35.492
- [laughs]

41:35.494 --> 41:36.559
Yeah.

41:36.561 --> 41:37.760
- Wouldn't be surprised.

41:45.604 --> 41:47.837
- Everyone,
the Reverend Brother's back!

41:47.839 --> 41:49.639
[indistinct chatter]

41:56.882 --> 41:59.182
- Devyn brought
an outside girl here,

41:59.184 --> 42:00.717
and she attracted
a flying beast.

42:00.719 --> 42:01.985
- No, she didn't.

42:01.987 --> 42:03.686
- It's possible
she controls the beast.

42:03.688 --> 42:04.888
It carried off
one of our cows.

42:04.890 --> 42:06.589
- This is crazy.

42:06.591 --> 42:09.659
- We are told the final days
will be a time of upheaval.

42:09.661 --> 42:13.563
We are called to charity
for its victims.

42:13.565 --> 42:16.533
<i> [ominous music]</i>

42:16.535 --> 42:18.268
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:18.270 --> 42:20.036
I will see her shortly.

42:20.038 --> 42:23.706
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:23.708 --> 42:26.142
- [whispering]
Oh, Matt, please come quick.

42:26.144 --> 42:28.845
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
